  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Wednesday. Science class today had four activities packed into one hour, and my brain is still trying to recover.",
      "zh": "星期三。今天理化課一個小時裡塞了四個活動，我的腦子到現在還在努力恢復。"
    },
    {
      "en": "First, we did a simple chemical experiment: mixing two colorless liquids together to see what would happen.",
      "zh": "第一項，我們做了一個簡單的化學實驗：把兩種無色的液體混合在一起，看看會發生什麼事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The moment I stirred the mixture, it turned a bright, glowing blue, and half the class gasped like we had discovered magic.",
      "zh": "我一攪拌那個混合物，它馬上變成一種鮮豔發亮的藍色，全班有一半的人倒吸一口氣，好像我們發現了魔法一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This is not magic,\" our teacher said, smiling. \"This is cause and effect. One chemical causes a reaction, and the color change is the result.\"",
      "zh": "「這不是魔法，」老師笑著說：「這是因果關係，一種化學物質造成反應，顏色改變就是結果。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She explained that even something as small as temperature can be a factor that changes how fast the reaction happens.",
      "zh": "她解釋，就連溫度這種小小的東西，都可能是影響反應速度快慢的一個因素。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next, we moved on to a station about electric energy, where we built a tiny circuit using a battery, some wire, and a small electrical motor.",
      "zh": "接著，我們移到電力能量的站，用電池、電線，還有一顆小小的電動馬達，組了一個小電路。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When I connected the wires correctly, the little engine spun to life, and I felt genuinely proud of myself for two whole seconds.",
      "zh": "當我把電線接對的時候，那顆小小的引擎就轉了起來，我真的為自己感到驕傲了整整兩秒鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This tiny engine works the same basic way as much bigger machines,\" the teacher said. \"Only the size and the technology are different.\"",
      "zh": "「這顆小小的引擎，運作原理跟更大型的機器基本上一樣，」老師說：「只是大小跟科技不一樣而已。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She reminded us that every machine, no matter how advanced its technology, still needs some kind of system to make it function properly.",
      "zh": "她提醒我們，不管一台機器的科技多先進，它還是需要某種系統，才能正常運作。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Third came a quick review of the human body: cells, the tiny basic units of life, and organs, which are made of many cells working together.",
      "zh": "第三個活動是快速複習人體：細胞，也就是生命最基本的小小單位，以及器官，由許多細胞一起合作組成。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Scientists did not always know cells existed,\" she said. \"Someone had to discover them first, using an early kind of microscope.\"",
      "zh": "「科學家並不是一開始就知道細胞存在，」她說：「一定有人先用早期的顯微鏡發現了它們。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That discovery, she explained, completely changed how doctors understood the human body and every organ inside it.",
      "zh": "她解釋，那項發現徹底改變了醫生對人體，以及裡面每一個器官的理解方式。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Finally, our last station was about the environment: we had to collect data on how much paper our class throws away in one single day.",
      "zh": "最後一站是關於環境：我們要蒐集數據，記錄我們班一天到底丟掉多少紙張。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's class, apparently, is doing something similar, collecting environmental data on the whole school for a bigger project.",
      "zh": "顯然 William 那個班級也在做類似的事，蒐集全校的環境數據，做一個更大的專案。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Good data does not lie,\" the teacher said. \"If we produce this much paper waste every day, we need a system to reduce it.\"",
      "zh": "「好的數據不會說謊，」老師說：「如果我們每天製造這麼多紙張垃圾，我們就需要一套系統來減少它。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice suggested we create a small recycling station right outside our classroom, and the teacher actually seemed to like the idea.",
      "zh": "Bernice 提議我們在教室外面弄一個小小的回收站，老師似乎真的滿喜歡這個提議。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of class, my notebook was full of chemical reactions, electric circuits, human cells, and recycling data, all crammed onto one page.",
      "zh": "下課的時候，我的筆記本上塞滿了化學反應、電路、人體細胞跟回收數據，全都擠在同一頁上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I told Bernice that today's class felt less like one subject and more like four different classes wearing a lab coat.",
      "zh": "我跟 Bernice 說，今天這堂課感覺不像一門課，比較像四門不同的課穿著同一件實驗衣一起上課。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: science somehow connects glowing blue liquid, tiny engines, human cells, and our classroom trash can, all in one single hour.",
      "zh": "今日心得：科學不知怎麼地，能把發亮的藍色液體、小小的引擎、人體細胞，還有我們教室的垃圾桶，全部連結在同一個小時裡。"
    }
  ],
